<Retconned>

I'm flattered that you're asking me of all writers. Well, hm. This isn't much of an issue given that my works are interactive, but...

If a scene feels like it's dragging too long, try giving the characters a sudden reason to exit. Be it a phone ringing in the other room, the appearance of a friend, the love interest getting sleepy...

Basically any excuse to end the scene. The trick is in doing this naturally. If it's a conversation, answer all open questions, then have the interruption occur. If it's NOT a conversation, it's even easier to cap things off.

Hope that helps!
